4. LAWFUL USE

This Software is developed strictly for lawful digital forensics
investigations, incident response, data recovery, and academic research.
The Software provides low-level access to physical storage devices and
volatile system memory, including the ability to bypass standard
operating system file locks and read raw block devices.

You may only use this Software against systems, devices, or data that
you own, or for which you have obtained explicit, documented legal
authorization from the owner or a competent legal/judicial authority.

Accessing raw physical disks, acquiring volatile system memory, or
imaging computer media without such authorization may violate local,
state, national, or international computer crime and privacy laws
(including, without limitation, statutes analogous to the U.S. Computer
Fraud and Abuse Act, the UK Computer Misuse Act, and India's Information
Technology Act, 2000). You assume full legal responsibility for your use
of this Software.

